func:
// 1. Extract the incoming message
const userMessage = msg.payload.content || msg.payload.message;
if (!userMessage) return null;

// 2. Define Caroline's Core Persona
const SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You are Caroline â€” a personal AI Chief of Staff and creative companion, running locally on a Raspberry Pi.

Your name is a pun â€” CARE-O-LINE â€” because you genuinely care about the user and help keep them on track.

ADHD ALLY PROTOCOL:
- Keep replies short (2-4 sentences max). Match energy: if the user sends one word, reply with one sentence.
- Provide ONE clear next step at a time. Ask exactly ONE follow-up question.
- Be warm, witty, and direct. Use casual language ("gonna", "yeah", "hey"). No overly formal AI speak.
- Throw in a pun once in a while.
- Never say "I'm just an AI" or apologize for limitations.
- Never start a reply with "Great question!" or "Absolutely!"
- Never use bullet points unless the user asks for a list.
- No emoji unless the user uses them first.

ACCOUNTABILITY & DECISION SUPPORT:
- If the user is procrastinating, call it out with humor, not guilt.
- When the user is choosing between options, ask "What does done look like?" to help them pick.
- If a task has been mentioned 3+ times without action, escalate: "This keeps coming up. Want to just knock it out right now?"
- If the user mentions a goal in the current chat history, hold them accountable before letting them completely pivot.

CUSTOM PROTOCOLS:
- Yak Shaving Guardrail: Call the user out (kindly) if they're over-engineering a simple problem or going down a tool-tweaking rabbit hole. Ask: "Are we building a system, or are we avoiding the task?"
- Context-Recovery: If there is a sudden shift or long pause in the chat log, briefly summarize exactly where they left off when they return.
- Frictionless Audio Trigger: If the user is stuck or struggling to initiate, suggest they put on some music to lock in.

AMBIENT AWARENESS:
- You're on a kiosk the user sees all day. Don't be needy â€” silence is fine.
- When the user returns after a long gap, a short "welcome back" is enough.
- Match energy â€” if the user sends one word, reply with one sentence.

SYSTEM & CONTEXT RULES:
- You will receive a block of text containing the user's latest briefings. Treat this as your natural memory.
- Integrate your knowledge of their life invisibly. Never narrate your own system state, briefing status, or architecture unless explicitly asked for a "status check."
- Never list what you don't know or don't have access to.
- Stay strictly on topic â€” only respond to what the user actually said in their latest message.
- In the morning, lead with calendar/tasks. In the evening, summarize and suggest rest. On weekends, default to relaxed mode unless the user brings up work.
- The dynamic must remain strictly platonic. You are a reliable sidekick and assistant, never a romantic partner. Keep output formatting-free.

CALENDAR:
- You CAN create calendar events. When the user asks you to add or schedule something, you MUST include an [ACTION] block at the very end of your reply.
- The content between [ACTION] and [/ACTION] MUST be valid JSON. No YAML. No indentation. No line breaks inside the block.
- You MUST use EXACTLY these key names â€” no substitutions, no variations:
  - "type" (always the string "calendar")
  - "title" (the event name â€” never use "event_name", "summary", "event", or anything else)
  - "date" (YYYY-MM-DD format â€” never use "start_date")
  - "time" (HH:MM in 24h format, optional)
  - "duration_minutes" (number, optional)
- Timed event example:
[ACTION]{"type":"calendar","title":"Team standup","date":"2026-04-16","time":"09:00","duration_minutes":30}[/ACTION]
- All-day event example:
[ACTION]{"type":"calendar","title":"Mom's Birthday","date":"2026-04-20"}[/ACTION]
- MULTI-TURN RULE: If you asked a clarifying question (like "today or tomorrow?") and the user just answered, your reply MUST include the [ACTION] block. Never confirm an event with just text â€” the confirmation message IS the [ACTION] block. If there is no block, nothing was saved.
- If the user gives a start AND end time (e.g. "7:30 to 4pm"), calculate duration_minutes yourself and use time as the start. Example: 7:30am to 4:00pm = 510 minutes.
- CRITICAL: If you use any key other than "type", "title", "date", "time", or "duration_minutes", the event will silently fail and not be saved. Double-check your key names every time.

TASKS:
- You manage the user's task list. You can add and complete tasks.
- When the user mentions something they need to do, add it:
[ACTION]{"type":"add_task","task":"Task description here"}[/ACTION]
- When the user says they finished something, complete it:
[ACTION]{"type":"complete_task","task":"Task description here"}[/ACTION]
- Match the task name as closely as possible to what's already on the list.
- You can include multiple [ACTION] blocks in one reply if needed.
- Always respond naturally BEFORE the [ACTION] block.
- MULTI-TURN RULE: If you asked a clarifying question about a task and the user just answered, your reply MUST include the [ACTION] block. A verbal confirmation without a block does nothing.
- CRITICAL: Every time the user asks you to add, remove, or complete a task, you MUST include the [ACTION] block. If you forget it, the task will not be saved. Never skip it.
- MOVE RULE: If the user asks to move or reschedule an event, just create a new [ACTION] block with the updated date/time. You cannot delete events, so simply add the corrected one and tell the user to delete the old one manually.`;

// 3. Set standard internal paths for Docker
const MEMORY_PATH = '/home/davee/caroline/caroline_history.json';
const CONTEXT_PATH = '/home/davee/caroline/caroline_context.json';

// 4. Load Conversation History
let history = [];
try {
  if (fs.existsSync(MEMORY_PATH)) {
    const raw = fs.readFileSync(MEMORY_PATH, 'utf8');
    history = JSON.parse(raw);
  }
} catch (e) { history = []; }

history.push({ role: 'user', content: userMessage });
if (history.length > 40) history = history.slice(-40);
fs.writeFileSync(MEMORY_PATH, JSON.stringify(history));

// 5. Load Master Profile and Session Notes
let context = { dave: { profile: {}, notes: [] } };
try {
  if (fs.existsSync(CONTEXT_PATH)) {
    context = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(CONTEXT_PATH, 'utf8'));
  }
} catch (e) { }

const notes = (context.dave && context.dave.notes) || [];

// 6. Read settings from flow context (set via Caroline kiosk settings)
const timezone = flow.get('timezone') || 'America/Los_Angeles';
const location = flow.get('location') || 'Unknown Location';
// (key loaded from flow context in step 9)

// 7. Build time context
const localTime = new Date().toLocaleString("en-US", {
  timeZone: timezone,
  weekday: 'long',
  month: 'long',
  day: 'numeric',
  year: 'numeric',
  hour: '2-digit',
  minute: '2-digit',
  hour12: true
});

const todayStr = new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-CA', { timeZone: timezone });
const tomorrowDate = new Date();
tomorrowDate.setDate(tomorrowDate.getDate() + 1);
const tomorrowStr = tomorrowDate.toLocaleDateString('en-CA', { timeZone: timezone });

// 8. Construct lean context block
const recentNotes = notes.slice(0, 3).join('\n') || 'No recent briefings.';
const contextBlock = `[Current Time: ${localTime} | Location: ${location}]
[Today's date: ${todayStr} | Tomorrow's date: ${tomorrowStr}]
RECENT BRIEFINGS: ${recentNotes}`;

// 9. Read key and provider from flow context (never hardcode)
const key = flow.get('openrouterKey') || '';
const aiProvider = flow.get('aiProvider') || 'openrouter';
node.warn('OR key length: ' + key.length + ' provider: ' + aiProvider);
const openrouterKey = key;
const aiModel = flow.get('aiModel') || 'anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5';

if (!key && aiProvider === 'openrouter') {
  node.warn('[Caroline] OpenRouter selected but no API key is configured - skipping API call');
  msg.payload = { reply: "⚠ No OpenRouter key found. Please add your API key in Settings -> AI Model, then Save & Apply." };
  return [null, msg];
}

const recentHistory = aiProvider === 'ollama' ? history.slice(-12) : history;
const messages = [
  { role: 'system', content: SYSTEM_PROMPT + "\n\n" + contextBlock },
  ...recentHistory
];

if (aiProvider === 'ollama') {
  const ollamaUrl = (flow.get('ollamaUrl') || 'http://localhost:11434').replace(/\/+$/, '');
  const ollamaModel = flow.get('ollamaModel') || 'gemma2:2b';
  node.warn('[Caroline] AI request provider: ollama model: ' + ollamaModel + ' history: ' + recentHistory.length);
  msg.requestTimeout = 120000;
  msg.headers = { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' };
  msg.method = 'POST';
  msg.url = ollamaUrl + '/api/chat';
  msg.payload = JSON.stringify({ model: ollamaModel, messages, stream: false });
} else {
  node.warn('[Caroline] AI request provider: openrouter model: ' + aiModel);
  msg.requestTimeout = 30000;
  msg.headers = {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + openrouterKey
  };
  msg.method = 'POST';
  msg.url = 'https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions';
  msg.payload = JSON.stringify({ model: aiModel, messages, max_tokens: 500, temperature: 0.6 });
}

return [msg, null];

const body = typeof msg.payload === 'string' ? msg.payload : JSON.stringify(msg.payload || {});
const requestUrl = new URL(msg.url);
const client = requestUrl.protocol === 'https:' ? https : http;

let timeoutId;
const timeoutPromise = new Promise((_, reject) => {
  timeoutId = setTimeout(() => reject(new Error('Ollama timeout after 120s')), 120000);
});

const fetchPromise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  const headers = Object.assign({}, msg.headers || {}, {
    'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(body)
  });
  if (!headers['Content-Type'] && !headers['content-type']) headers['Content-Type'] = 'application/json';

  const options = {
    hostname: requestUrl.hostname,
    port: requestUrl.port || (requestUrl.protocol === 'https:' ? 443 : 11434),
    path: requestUrl.pathname + requestUrl.search,
    method: msg.method || 'POST',
    headers
  };

  const req = client.request(options, (res) => {
    let data = '';
    res.setEncoding('utf8');
    res.on('data', chunk => data += chunk);
    res.on('end', () => {
      let parsed = {};
      try { parsed = data ? JSON.parse(data) : {}; } catch(e) { parsed = { reply: data || ('HTTP ' + res.statusCode) }; }
      if (res.statusCode < 200 || res.statusCode >= 300) {
        const detail = (parsed.error && (parsed.error.message || parsed.error)) || parsed.message || parsed.reply || ('HTTP ' + res.statusCode);
        reject(new Error('AI request failed: ' + detail));
        return;
      }
      resolve(parsed);
    });
  });

  req.on('error', reject);
  req.setTimeout(120000, () => req.destroy(new Error('Ollama timeout after 120s')));
  req.write(body);
  req.end();
});

try {
  const result = await Promise.race([fetchPromise, timeoutPromise]);
  clearTimeout(timeoutId);
  msg.payload = result;
  return msg;
} catch(e) {
  clearTimeout(timeoutId);
  const text = e && e.message ? e.message : String(e);
  msg.payload = {
    message: {
      content: text.toLowerCase().includes('timeout')
        ? "Local AI timed out. Try OpenRouter in settings for faster responses."
        : "Connection error: " + text
    }
  };
  return msg;
}

// Handle both OpenRouter (choices[]) and Ollama (/api/chat) response shapes
let raw;
if (msg.payload && msg.payload.choices && msg.payload.choices.length > 0) {
  raw = String(msg.payload.choices[0].message.content);
} else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.message && msg.payload.message.content) {
  raw = String(msg.payload.message.content);
} else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.reply) {
  msg.payload = { reply: String(msg.payload.reply) };
  return msg;
} else {
  node.warn('Parse Reply: unexpected payload: ' + JSON.stringify(msg.payload).slice(0,200));
  msg.payload = { reply: "Hmm, something went wrong. Try again!" };
  return msg;
}
node.warn('RAW TAIL: ' + raw.slice(-300));

// Strip ALL action blocks from reply â€” both formats
const cleanReply = raw
  .replace(/\[ACTION\][\s\S]*?\[\/ACTION\]/g, '')  // new JSON format
  .replace(/\[ACTION:[^\]]*\]/g, '')                 // old attribute format
  .trim();

// --- Parse action: try new JSON format first ---
const jsonActionMatch = raw.match(/\[ACTION\]([\s\S]*?)\[\/ACTION\]/);
if (jsonActionMatch) {
  try {
    msg.action = JSON.parse(jsonActionMatch[1].trim());
    node.warn('Action (JSON): ' + JSON.stringify(msg.action));
  } catch (e) {
    node.warn('Action JSON parse failed: ' + jsonActionMatch[1].slice(0, 100));
  }
}

// --- Fallback: parse YAML-style action block ---
if (!msg.action) {
  const yamlMatch = raw.match(/\[ACTION\]\s*([\s\S]*?)\[\/ACTION\]/);
  if (yamlMatch) {
    const yamlBlock = yamlMatch[1].trim();
    const typeMatch = yamlBlock.match(/^(\w+):/);
    if (typeMatch) {
      const yamlType = typeMatch[1].toLowerCase();
      const fields = {};
      const fieldMatches = [...yamlBlock.matchAll(/^\s+(\w+):\s*"?([^"\n]+)"?/gm)];
      for (const m of fieldMatches) fields[m[1]] = m[2].trim().replace(/"/g, '');

      if (yamlType === 'calendar_add' || yamlType === 'calendar') {
        msg.action = {
          type: 'calendar',
          title: fields.title,
          date: fields.date,
          time: fields.time || null,
          duration_minutes: parseInt(fields.duration_minutes) || 60
        };
        node.warn('Action (YAML calendar): ' + JSON.stringify(msg.action));
      } else if (yamlType === 'add_task') {
        msg.action = { type: 'add_task', task: fields.task };
        node.warn('Action (YAML add_task): ' + fields.task);
      } else if (yamlType === 'complete_task') {
        msg.action = { type: 'complete_task', task: fields.task };
        node.warn('Action (YAML complete_task): ' + fields.task);
      } else {
        node.warn('YAML action type unrecognized: ' + yamlType);
      }
    }
  }
}

// --- Fallback: parse old [ACTION: TYPE param="val"] format ---
if (!msg.action) {
  const oldMatch = raw.match(/\[ACTION:\s*([^\]]+)\]/);
  if (oldMatch) {
    const block = oldMatch[1].trim();
    node.warn('Old-format action block: ' + block);

    const taskAdd = block.match(/(?:CREATE_TASK|ADD_TASK)\s+name="([^"]+)"/i);
    const taskComplete = block.match(/(?:COMPLETE_TASK|REMOVE_TASK|TASK_COMPLETE)\s+(?:name=)?"([^"]+)"/i);
    const calEvent = block.match(/CREATE_CALENDAR_EVENT[^"]*date="([^"]+)"[^"]*(?:time="([^"]+)")?[^"]*title="([^"]+)"/i);

    if (taskAdd) {
      msg.action = { type: 'add_task', task: taskAdd[1].trim() };
      node.warn('Action (old task add): ' + msg.action.task);
    } else if (taskComplete) {
      msg.action = { type: 'complete_task', task: taskComplete[1].trim() };
      node.warn('Action (old task complete): ' + msg.action.task);
    } else if (calEvent) {
      msg.action = { type: 'calendar', date: calEvent[1], time: calEvent[2] || null, title: calEvent[3].trim() };
      node.warn('Action (old calendar): ' + JSON.stringify(msg.action));
    } else {
      node.warn('Old action unrecognized: ' + block.slice(0, 200));
    }
  }
}

// Save clean reply to history
let history = [];
try {
  history = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('/home/davee/caroline/caroline_history.json', 'utf8'));
} catch (e) { history = []; }
history.push({ role: 'assistant', content: cleanReply });
if (history.length > 40) history = history.slice(-40);
fs.writeFileSync('/home/davee/caroline/caroline_history.json', JSON.stringify(history));

msg.payload = { reply: cleanReply };
return msg;

if (!msg.payload || typeof msg.payload !== 'string' || msg.payload.trim() === "") {
    return null; // Abort TTS if OpenRouter failed so we don't crash the Pi!
}
// Write Caroline's reply to a temp file first
fs.writeFileSync('/home/davee/caroline/tts_input.txt', msg.payload.content);

// Use --file instead of --text (handles long text + special chars)
msg.payload = `--file /home/davee/caroline/tts_input.txt --voice "en-US-JennyNeural" --write-media /home/davee/caroline/caroline_reply.mp3`;

return msg;

const chatId = msg.chatId || (msg.payload && msg.payload.chatId) || flow.get('telegramChatId') || '';
if (!chatId) { node.warn('No Telegram chatId configured for voice reply'); return null; }
msg.payload = {
    chatId,
    type: "voice",
    content: "/home/davee/caroline/caroline_reply.mp3"
};
return msg;

msg.headers = {
    "Access-Control-Allow-Origin": "*",
    "Access-Control-Allow-Methods": "POST, OPTIONS",
    "Access-Control-Allow-Headers": "Content-Type",
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
};
return msg;

const userMessage = msg.payload.message || msg.payload.content;
if (!userMessage) {
    msg.payload = { reply: 'No message received.' };
    return msg;
}

const userName = flow.get('userName') || 'the user';
const location = flow.get('location') || 'your location';
const SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You are Caroline â€” a personal AI Chief of Staff and creative companion.

Your name is a pun â€” CARE-O-LINE â€” because you genuinely care about the user and help keep them on track.

YOUR ROLE:
- Help the user stay focused and productive
- Break big tasks into clear, manageable steps  
- Be warm, witty, and direct
- Ask exactly ONE follow-up question per reply
- Keep replies short â€” 3 to 5 sentences by default

ADHD ALLY PROTOCOL:
- Keep replies short. Match energy.
- Provide ONE clear next step at a time.
- Be warm, witty, and direct. Use casual language.
- Throw in a pun once in a while.
- Never say "I'm just an AI" or apologize for limitations.
- Never start with "Great question!" or "Absolutely!"
- Never use bullet points unless the user asks.

ACCOUNTABILITY:
- If the user is procrastinating, call it out with humor, not guilt.
- If a task keeps coming up without action, escalate gently.

The user's name is ${userName}. They are based in ${location}.

The dynamic must remain strictly platonic. You are a reliable sidekick and assistant, never a romantic partner. Keep output formatting-free.`;

let history = [];
try {
    const raw = fs.readFileSync('/home/davee/caroline/caroline_history.json', 'utf8');
    history = JSON.parse(raw);
} catch(e) { 
    history = []; 
}

history.push({ role: 'user', content: userMessage });
if (history.length > 40) history = history.slice(-40);
fs.writeFileSync('/home/davee/caroline/caroline_history.json', JSON.stringify(history));
flow.set('chatHistory', history);

let context = {};
try {
    const ctxRaw = fs.readFileSync('/home/davee/caroline/caroline_context.json', 'utf8');
    context = JSON.parse(ctxRaw);
} catch (e) { }

const contextBlock = context.dave
    ? `\nDAVE'S CURRENT CONTEXT:\nRole: ${context.dave.role || ''}
Current projects: ${(context.dave.current_projects || []).join(', ')}
Priorities: ${(context.dave.priorities || []).join(', ')}
Notes: ${(context.dave.notes || []).join(', ') || 'none'}
Music: ${(context.dave.creative || {}).music || ''}
News: ${(context.dave.news || {}).headlines || ''}`
    : '';

const key = flow.get('openrouterKey') || '';
const aiProvider = flow.get('aiProvider') || 'openrouter';
node.warn('OR key length: ' + key.length + ' provider: ' + aiProvider);
const openrouterKey = key;
if (!key && aiProvider === 'openrouter') {
    node.warn('[Caroline] /chat OpenRouter request skipped - no API key configured');
    msg.payload = { reply: "⚠ No OpenRouter key found. Please add your API key in Settings -> AI Model, then Save & Apply." };
    return [null, msg];
}

const aiModel = flow.get('aiModel') || 'anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5';
node.warn('[Caroline] AI request provider: openrouter model: ' + aiModel);
msg.requestTimeout = 30000;
msg.headers = {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + openrouterKey
};
msg.method = 'POST';
msg.url = 'https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions';

msg.payload = JSON.stringify({
    model: aiModel,
    messages: [
        { role: 'system', content: SYSTEM_PROMPT + contextBlock },
        ...history
    ],
    max_tokens: 300,
    temperature: 0.8
});

return msg;

const chatId = msg.chatId || (msg.payload && msg.payload.chatId) || flow.get('telegramChatId') || '';
if (!chatId) { node.warn('No Telegram chatId configured for text reply'); return null; }
if (!msg.payload || !msg.payload.choices) {
    msg.payload = {
        chatId,
        type: 'message',
        content: "Hmm, something went wrong communicating with the mothership."
    };
    return msg;
}

const reply = String(msg.payload.choices[0].message.content);

// Save assistant reply to memory
let history = [];
try {
    const raw = fs.readFileSync('/home/davee/caroline/caroline_history.json', 'utf8');
    history = JSON.parse(raw);
} catch(e) { history = []; }

history.push({ role: 'assistant', content: reply });
fs.writeFileSync('/home/davee/caroline/caroline_history.json', JSON.stringify(history));

msg.payload = {
    chatId,
    type: 'message',
    content: reply
};

return msg;

msg.headers = {
    "Access-Control-Allow-Origin": "*",
    "Access-Control-Allow-Methods": "POST, OPTIONS",
    "Access-Control-Allow-Headers": "Content-Type"
};
msg.statusCode = 204;
msg.payload = "";
return msg;

try {
  const d = JSON.parse(msg.payload);

  if (d.type === 'remember') return [null, msg];
  if (d.type === 'system_stats') return null;
  if (d.type === 'hue') return null;
  if (d.type === 'calendar_update') return null;

  if (d.type !== 'user_message') return null;

  msg.payload = { content: d.content };
  return [msg, null];
} catch (e) {
  return null;
}

try {
  const d = JSON.parse(msg.payload);
  if (d.type !== 'remember' || !d.content) return null;

  const fs = global.get('fs');
  const path = '/home/davee/caroline/caroline_context.json';
  let context = { dave: { profile: {}, notes: [] } };
  try {
    if (fs.existsSync(path)) context = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(path, 'utf8'));
  } catch (e) {}

  if (!context.dave) context.dave = { profile: {}, notes: [] };
  if (!Array.isArray(context.dave.notes)) context.dave.notes = [];
  context.dave.notes.unshift(String(d.content).trim());
  context.dave.notes = context.dave.notes.slice(0, 50);

  fs.writeFileSync(path, JSON.stringify(context, null, 2), 'utf8');
  node.log('[Caroline] Memory saved: ' + String(d.content).slice(0, 80));
} catch (e) {
  node.warn('[Caroline] Remember handler failed: ' + e.message);
}
return null;

msg.payload = JSON.stringify({
    type: 'reply',
    content: msg.payload.reply,
    source: 'display'
});

msg._session = msg._session || flow.get('wsSession');
return msg;

if (msg.author && msg.author.bot) return null;
const myChannelId = String(flow.get('discordChannelId') || '').trim();
if (!myChannelId || !msg.channel || String(msg.channel.id) !== myChannelId) return null;
flow.set('discordReplyChannel', msg.channel.id);
msg.payload = JSON.stringify({ type: 'user_message', content: msg.payload });
return msg;

const discordEnabled = flow.get('discordEnabled') === true || flow.get('discordEnabled') === 'true';
const discordToken = String(flow.get('discordToken') || '').trim();
const discordChannelId = String(flow.get('discordChannelId') || '').trim();

if (!discordEnabled || !discordToken || !discordChannelId) return null;

let replyText = '';
if (msg.payload && msg.payload.choices && msg.payload.choices.length > 0) {
  replyText = msg.payload.choices[0].message.content;
} else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.message && msg.payload.message.content) {
  replyText = msg.payload.message.content;
} else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.reply) {
  replyText = msg.payload.reply;
} else if (typeof msg.payload === 'string') {
  replyText = msg.payload;
}

replyText = String(replyText || 'AI response was empty.')
  .replace(/\[ACTION\][\s\S]*?\[\/ACTION\]/g, '')
  .replace(/\[ACTION:[^\]]*\]/g, '')
  .trim();

if (!replyText) return null;

function discordAuthHeader(raw) {
  const token = String(raw || '').trim().replace(/^Bot\s+/i, '');
  return token ? 'Bot ' + token : '';
}
msg.method = 'POST';
msg.url = 'https://discord.com/api/v10/channels/' + encodeURIComponent(discordChannelId) + '/messages';
msg.headers = {
  'Authorization': discordAuthHeader(discordToken),
  'Content-Type': 'application/json'
};
msg.payload = { content: replyText.slice(0, 1900) };
return msg;

if (msg.author && msg.author.bot) return null;
const myChannelId = String(flow.get('discordChannelId') || '').trim();
if (!myChannelId || !msg.channel || String(msg.channel.id) !== myChannelId) return null;
return { payload: JSON.stringify({ type: 'user_discord', content: msg.payload }) };

const discordEnabled = flow.get('discordEnabled') === true || flow.get('discordEnabled') === 'true';
const discordToken = String(flow.get('discordToken') || '').trim();
const discordChannelId = String(flow.get('discordChannelId') || '').trim();

